% purity) and is typically used for investment purposes in the form of coins and bars.`},{key:"What is the 18K gold rate today in India?",value:`18K gold is trading at <strong>${n?`₹${n}`:"-"}</strong> per gram today. 18K gold contains 75% pure gold mixed with other metals, making it more durable and suitable for everyday jewellery.`},{key:"What is the reason for gold prices increasing in India?",value:"Gold prices rise due to geopolitical tensions, weakening rupee against the dollar, inflation concerns, and investors seeking safe-haven assets during economic uncertainty."},{key:"Will gold prices go down in India soon?",value:"Gold typically dips after festival seasons (Diwali, weddings) when demand drops, but exact timing is unpredictable as global events constantly influence markets."},{key:"What is a 22 CT gold hallmark, and how do I verify it?",value:'A 22K hallmark certifies 91.6% pure gold with a BIS logo and 6-digit code. Verify authenticity using the BIS CARE mobile app\'s "Verify HUID" feature.'},{key:"Why are gold rates different in different Indian cities?",value:"City-wise differences stem from transportation costs, local demand-supply dynamics, state taxes, and jewellers' margins—the gold quality remains the same."},{key:"Is gold still a good investment in India?",value:"Yes, gold is an excellent hedge against inflation and market volatility for long-term wealth creation. Use SGBs or ETFs for better returns than physical jewellery."}]}function s(){let e=arguments.length>0&&void 0!==arguments[0]?arguments[0]:[],t=arguments.length>1&&void 0!==arguments[1]?arguments[1]:[],o=(null==t?void 0:t[0])||{},a=(0,i.TU)(Number(null==o?void 0:o.price22Cr)),l=(0,i.TU)(Number(null==o?void 0:o.price24Cr)),n=(0,i.TU)(Number(null==o?void 0:o.price18Cr)),r={__GOLD24CARET__:l?`<strong>₹${l}</strong> per 10 gram`:"-",__GOLD22CARET__:a?`<strong>₹${a}</strong> per 10 gram`:"-",__GOLD18CARET__:n?`<strong>₹${n}</strong> per 10 gram`:"-"};return null==e?void 0:e.map(e=>({...e,val